  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers just flipped into BREAKOUT regime and are now short gamma with massive negative exposure at 6475 (-17.3B), meaning they're aggressively buying this dip as SPX sits just above that level at 6480.73, creating strong technical support. With spot trapped between the major negative gamma wall at 6475 (buying pressure) and positive gamma at 6490 (selling pressure), expect choppy but ultimately supported price action unless we break below 6475 where dealer buying accelerates. Key levels: break above 6490 triggers dealer selling into 6500/6515 resistance, while a flush below 6475 unleashes momentum-amplifying dealer purchases that could drive a sharp bounce back toward the GEX flip at 6410.",
